  "prompt": "I don't talk in English. How do I talk in English?",
  "response": "Learning to speak English can be an exciting journey! Here are some steps to help you get started:\n\n1. **Learn Basic Vocabulary**: Start with common words and phrases used in daily conversations. Flashcards or language apps can help.\n\n2. **Practice Pronunciation**: Listen to native speakers through movies, songs, or online videos. Repeat what you hear to practice your pronunciation.\n\n3. **Use Language Learning Apps**: Apps like Duolingo, Babbel, or Rosetta Stone can offer structured lessons and practice opportunities.\n\n4. **Take a Class**: If possible, enroll in an English language course. This will provide structured learning with a teacher.\n\n5. **Speak Regularly**: Practice speaking with friends who know English, or find conversation partners online. Websites like Tandem or HelloTalk can connect you with native speakers.\n\n6. **Think in English**: Try to think in English instead of your native language. This will improve your fluency.\n\n7. **Start a Journal**: Write short entries in English about your day. This helps with vocabulary and sentence structure.\n\n8. **Be Patient**: Learning a language takes time, so don\u2019t be discouraged by mistakes. They are part of the learning process!\n\nRemember, the key is consistent practice. Good luck!",
